  "prompt": "What are some good tips for essay writing?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful tips for essay writing:\n\n1. Understand the prompt\n- Read the assignment carefully\n- Identify key requirements and instructions\n\n2. Brainstorm and plan\n- Create an outline\n- Organize your thoughts\n- Develop a clear thesis statement\n\n3. Research thoroughly\n- Use credible sources\n- Take good notes\n- Keep track of references\n\n4. Write a strong introduction\n- Start with a compelling hook\n- Provide context\n- Include your thesis statement\n\n5. Develop clear body paragraphs\n- Use topic sentences\n- Provide evidence and examples\n- Explain your reasoning\n\n6. Maintain good structure\n- Follow a logical flow\n- Use transitions between paragraphs\n- Ensure coherence\n\n7. Write a strong conclusion\n- Restate your thesis\n- Summarize main points\n- Provide final insights\n\n8. Edit and proofread\n- Check for grammar and spelling\n- Ensure clarity\n- Read your essay out loud\n- Have someone else review it\n\n9. Cite sources properly\n- Use correct citation format\n- Avoid plagiarism\n- Give credit to original authors\n\n10. Practice and improve\n- Write regularly\n- Learn from feedback\n- Develop your writing skills",
